    "body": "- Replaced instances of T.gemm with T.wgmma_gemm and T.tcgen05_gemm in various example scripts to enhance performance and control over asynchronous execution.\r\n- Updated related documentation to reflect the changes in GEMM function usage, ensuring clarity on the new explicit interfaces.\r\n- Removed unnecessary wg_wait parameters from GEMM calls, aligning with the new function signatures.\r\n\r\nThis refactor improves the efficiency of matrix multiplication operations in the TileLang framework, particularly for Hopper and Blackwell architectures.\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Added new public GEMM variants: wgmma_gemm() and tcgen05_gemm().\n\n* **API Changes**\n  * Removed public wg_wait parameter; gemm() family is synchronous by default.\n  * tcgen05_gemm requires an explicit barrier argument and enforces target/ lowering constraints.\n  * Language/lowering interfaces accept an additional optional mbar-phase hint.\n\n* **Documentation**\n  * Updated examples and README to reflect new GEMM variants and sync semantics.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added CUDA tests covering wgmma/tcgen05 dispatch, sync, and lowering errors.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
